  "name": "Hello & Goodbye",
  "order": 1,
  "grammar_tips": [
    "Italian has both formal and informal greetings. Use 'ciao' with friends and family, and 'buongiorno' or 'buonasera' in formal situations or with strangers.",
    "'Ciao' is unique — it works as both 'hello' and 'goodbye', but only in informal settings.",
    "'Salve' is a safe middle ground when you're unsure whether to be formal or informal. It works at any time of day."
  ],
